DIV1.P:
I WOULD not give up, like Esau, Heb. xii. 16, 17.— my birth-right to seek a place of repentance with tears, and not find it. O my soul! for ever acknowledge how much thou owest unto thy LORD! Let none say
he hath blessed me variously, and in some future time I will awake my soul to gratitude. I have now something else to do;
like him who, when an apostle Acts xxiv. 25. reasoned of righteousness, temperance and judgment to come, replied go thy way for this time; when I have a conve∣nient season I will call for thee.
